The paper focuses on autonomous drone racing, which involves robotics and control (cs.RO), as well as computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for navigation and decision-making. The use of a vision-based navigation algorithm also suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulation results and theoretical analysis, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
